  <front>
   <head>EPITAPH ON MRS. SARAH MENCE.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">PEACE to the ashes, and the virtuous mind,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Of her who liv'd in peace with all mankind!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Humbly religious, silently sincere,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Humane to others, to herself severe.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Learn'd from the heart, unknowing of disguise,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Truth in her thoughts, and candour in her eyes;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Who sacrific'd no faith to private ends;</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Without reserve devoted to her friends.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Stranger alike to party and to pride,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Good sense her light, the word of God her guide;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">She gave to piety her early days,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And breath'd in dying hours her Maker's praise.</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Happy, who thus the soul to Heaven engage,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Their youth's first choice, their last desire in age.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
